In a large skillet, heat vegetable oil over medium-high heat. When oil is shiny, add ground chicken and season with salt and pepper. Brown chicken using a spatula to break into small pieces. Add chopped onion and saute until soft, about 2 minutes. Add Sun-Maid Golden Raisins and peanuts. Stir in sweet Thai chili sauce and lime juice; heat through, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and stir in cilantro. To serve, form a single lettuce leaf into a cup and spoon 2 to 3 tablespoons of chicken mixture into lettuce cup.